The paper discusses a continuation method for optimization, which is a common technique in machine learning and computer vision. The application of the method is demonstrated in the problem of nearest neighbor classification, which is a topic in machine learning and pattern recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method in terms of computational complexity, which suggests that it may be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
